<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->
## Summary by CodeRabbit

- **New Features**
  - Added the ability to view and manage a user's watchlist directly from the user table, including a responsive watchlist viewer with sorting, filtering, and pagination.
  - Introduced a "New User Defaults" form in the Utilities dashboard, allowing admins to set default sync permissions for new users.
  - Added a real-time progress updates endpoint for improved progress tracking of operations.
  - Added comprehensive rolling monitored shows management UI and controls, including reset and delete actions, with responsive tables and filtering.
  - Introduced session monitoring enhancements with auto-reset settings and manual controls for rolling monitored shows.
  - Added new API endpoints for managing rolling monitored shows, including reset and inactive show handling.

- **Enhancements**
  - Updated configuration options to support default settings for new users and rolling monitoring auto-reset.
  - Improved loading experience with skeleton screens for new utility forms.
  - Enhanced Plex and Sonarr integration with detailed episode-level management and improved series matching logic.
  - Refined progress event streaming and configuration parsing for better reliability.

- **Bug Fixes**
  - Adjusted disabled button styles in multi-select components for better accessibility.

- **Backend Improvements**
  - Added new API endpoints for user watchlists, progress streaming, and session monitoring.
  - Improved configuration handling for new user defaults and rolling monitoring settings.
  - Enhanced database schema with new columns for tracking rolling monitored shows updates.
  - Optimized event source connections for progress updates.
  - Added robust error handling and logging across session monitoring and Plex integration services.
<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->

**Automated Reviews**: Continuous reviews of the pull requests including incremental commits. 

**Summarization**: Generates high-level summary and a technical walkthrough of the PR changes. 

**Line-by-line review**: Provides line-by-line suggestions committable with one click.

**Codebase verification**:  Verifies the impact on the overall codebase and identifies missing changes.

**Insights into your code**:  Ask any questions on your codebase within the pull request 

**Chat about your code** : Chat with the bot around your code. The more you chat, the smarter it gets.

**Issue Validation**:  Validates the PR against the linked issues and identifies other related issues
